        "summary":  "AWS introduced the Claude apps gateway, a self-hosted control plane that centralizes governance of Claude Code and Claude Desktop access across enterprise developer populations. The gateway manages identity via OIDC SSO, enforces model and tool policies, tracks telemetry via OpenTelemetry, handles multi-region routing, and applies granular spend caps ΓÇö all without per-developer credentials or static secrets. It deploys as a stateless container on ECS, EKS, or EC2 with a PostgreSQL backend and supports routing through either Amazon Bedrock or Claude Platform on AWS.",
